settings.footer-text: RN Interior Design is a full-service interior design studio specializing in high end residential design. Guided by story, timelessness, and character, RN designs innovative spaces for new builds and remodels across the globe.

settings.headings: Expert, holistic interior design for spaces that tell stories.

settings.buy-text1: At RN Interior Design, we serve clients looking to design high-end spaces for new builds and full home remodels. With a focus on luxury, uniqueness, and timelessness, we design the home you’ve always dreamed of — and we bring you along at every step for and—seamless and intentional experience.

settings.buy-text1: Our signature interior masterpieces go through a holistic, full-service design process from conception to completion. Here’s a look at some of our latest completed projects:
Our expert design team, led by Rania Nasser, serves clients globally with one mission at heart: to create functional, beautiful and approachable interiors.

settings.title1: RN Interior Design is a full service design firm that specializes in residential high-end interior design both locally and internationally.
settings.title2:
Over the last 10 years, RN Interior Design studio has become known and respected for creating modern, classic interiors with a European flair, heavily-shaped by Rania’s multi-cultural background.

Our projects include a varied range of styles, centered on creating functional, beautiful and approachable spaces. A highly personalized and collaborative process is the foundation of our work. We pride ourselves on attentively listening to our clients’ needs and preferences to help customize their personal space. Our philosophy has always been to keep the design process seamless and enjoyable. We strive in setting the client space apart from the ordinary through thoughtful design, distinct details and respect for quality.

RN Interior Design studio’s main goal is to inspire clients, and introduce them to elegant, innovative design that ultimately enhances their well-being.

settings.buy-text2: With approved mood boards, we start diving into the details of your space — from wall treatments to ceiling details to materials and elevations. We’ll consider the major architectural elements in the home, identify focal points and start assigning preliminary materials and finishes.

This phase is highly important and detailed in our interior design process. Our team works collaboratively along the way to inspire one another, share ideas and choose the plans and pieces that reflect our discovery phase and mood boards.

We develop key elevations that convey each design concept using 2D and 3D renderings to show scale, contrast and balance. We incorporate plumbing, lighting and materials to show a holistic view of the prominent areas of your project.

settings.title: Start the interior design process with RN Interior Design

settings.buy-text2:
Our research and discovery phase
kicks off as our team works to start defining and telling your story. We use everything from local cultural influences and conversation to start selecting
concepts for each room.
Using color stories, look & feel as well as inspiration imagery, we create mood boards that encompass the overall vibe and vision of the rooms and details of your design.
This helps us align on style before proceeding with Design Development.
After we’ve decided to work together, welike to meet with you (ideally in person)to start strengthening our relationship and creating some magic together.

We’ll dive into the scope of your project as well as talk about your budget and timeline — and then we’ll start learning more about you, your likes/dislikes, and the overall vision for your space.

In the consultation phase, we’re working together to define the parameters of your style and scope to make sure that we’re on the right track before beginning the design nitty-gritty

Once the design is approved, we apply it to a drawing set for the general contractor to build off of. This includes floor plans, ceiling plans, furniture placement plans, floor finish plans, schedules, elevations, details and even demolition plans if necessary.

settings.title: CONSTRUCTION DOCUMENTATION
settings.buy-text8:
The construction documents cover every aspect of the project to clearly communicate our design and vision.

Before construction kicks off, we complete final alignment and coordination with all disciplines involved in your project including architects, lighting designers, mechanical engineers, A/V consultants and electricians to name a few.

settings.buy-text2: Once your interior drawings have been issued, we continue coordinating with construction to keep every step of your project on track, schedule and budget — and to ensure that your thoughtful design is being executed according to our drawing set and standards.

During construction administration, we pay special attention to sourcing and fulfillment. If a tile is discontinued or a light fixture’s lead time is extended, we’ll re-source selections and meet the pace of construction.

During this phase, we coordinate and continue reviewing shop drawings of fireplaces, metal work, cabinetry and millwork — answer any questions and address any problems that may arise.

While construction is well underway, our team embarks on the FF&A — furniture, fixtures and accessories — before process to expand on the design with hand-selected, curated and often custom pieces aligned with your design. This includes putting together a furniture budget, laying out each room and sourcing materials and finishes.

We source from some of our trade-favorites, local showrooms and custom vendors to create a medley of furnishings customized for your space. This also includes selections of decorative lighting, window treatments, art, linens and accessories.


Our team infuses our experience and expertise to pull every piece together in a balanced, harmonious way that’s super-tailored to your unique project — and then we’ll show you a comprehensive overview for approval in an interactive presentation that includes fabrics, leathers and finishes to both feel and see.
After the FF&A selections are finalized and budget approved, we order items through our in-house purchasing department and stay in contact with our vendors to stay informed on each order.
We verify that each piece is in perfect condition before overseeing and managing any necessary transport to your space.

settings.title: Furniture Installation
settings.buy-text2:
This is the most exciting phase of the project. This is when we see it all come together! As construction comes to a close, we schedule an install day that works with you, the builder and the receiving warehouse.

Our team directs the exact placement of all items within each room. The finishing touch comes with accessorizing and styling. Depending on the size of the project, this could be a multi-day process.

settings.top-text: Our design process dives deep to create breathtaking Interiors and we’d love to start crafting yours!
settings.buy-text2: Our signature interiors are modern yet classic — and are completely tailored to your vision and space. As a collaborative team, we design your home to speak to your taste and tell your story like only art can.
